Sentencas: A-site deficiency was introduced intentionally into the mixed conducting perovskite ABO(3)-type oxide, La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF=6/4/2/8), in order to create additional oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Introduction of A-site deficiency into La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and its effect on structure and conductivity

Sentencas: With increasing Sr-deficiency, z in La0.6Sr0.4-zCo0.2Fe0.8O3-delta, its lattice parameters and oxygen content gradually increased and decreased, respectively, which strongly suggested that additional oxygen vacancies were created in the lattice.
Titulo: Introduction of A-site deficiency into La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and its effect on structure and conductivity

Sentencas: It is expected that these additional oxygen vacancies improve its oxide ionic conductivity and catalytic property for oxygen reduction.
Titulo: Introduction of A-site deficiency into La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and its effect on structure and conductivity

Sentencas: Further increase in z, however, led the LSCF system into a coexistence region with transition metal oxides.
Titulo: Introduction of A-site deficiency into La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and its effect on structure and conductivity

Sentencas: In the wide range of P(O-2), electrical property of samples 0.00 <= z <= 0.025 was p-type semi-conducting regardless of the z value, whereas its conductivity was strongly affected by a subtle change in z. (c) 2005
Titulo: Introduction of A-site deficiency into La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and its effect on structure and conductivity
